'''平开窗'''（{{lang-en|casement window}}）是一種窗戶，該窗戶的一側會通過一个或多个[[铰链|铰链]]与窗框相连<ref>{{cite book |last       = 
 |first      = 
 |author1    = Poppeliers, Chamers, Jr.
 |author2    = Schwartz
 |url        = https://archive.org/details/whatstyleisitgui00popp_0/page/98
 |title      = What Style is it?
 |publisher  = John Wiley and Sons
 |year       = 1983
 |location   = NY
 |pages      = [https://archive.org/details/whatstyleisitgui00popp_0/page/98 98]
 |doi        = 
 |id         = 
 |isbn       = 0-471-14434-7
}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sashwindow.com/images/pdfs/infographics/timber_window_type_comparison.jpg|title=Casement window vs sash window comparison|website=The Sash Window Workshop|accessdate=2020-07-08|archive-date=2020-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401231122/http://www.sashwindow.com/images/pdfs/infographics/timber_window_type_comparison.jpg|dead-url=no}}</ref>。窗框內可以安裝一扇平开窗或兩扇對開的平開窗。平开窗通常使用平开窗撑（{{lang-en|casement stay}}）保持打开状态。顶部铰接的窗户称为上悬窗，底部铰接的窗户称为下悬窗<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sahaha.cn/clks/5731.html|title=盘点平开窗、推拉窗、上悬式窗、对开窗的区别及优缺点 - 广州雪亚窗帘|website=广州雪亚窗帘|access-date=2020-70-07|archive-date=2020-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200711004453/http://www.sahaha.cn/clks/5731.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
==历史==
在英国，平开窗在引入推拉窗之前很常见。它们通常由玻璃板和铅条固定<ref>{{cite web
 |url=https://www.quotestocompare.com/windows/casement-windows
 |title=Casement window 
 |publisher=Illustrated Architectural Dictionary 
 |accessdate=2008-01-18 
 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071224035434/http://ah.bfn.org/a/DCTNRY/c/casement.html 
 |archivedate=2007-12-24 
}}
</ref>。这些平开窗通常在侧面铰接，并向内打开。
